
 - ref - http://clojure.com/blog/2013/06/28/clojure-core-async-channels.html

 - core.async -
 ---------------
 - Decouples channels and processes (go blocks) 
 - Push, Pull, or a mix are possible. 
 
 - message oriented -
 ------------------------
 - core.async is message oriented
 - Hence, granular & more flexible
 
 - concurrency vs parallelsim -
 ------------------------------------
 - ref - http://blog.golang.org/concurrency-is-not-parallelism
 - In programming, concurrency is the composition of independently executing processes, 
 - while parallelism is the simultaneous execution of (possibly related) computations. 
 - Concurrency is about dealing with lots of things at once. 
 - Parallelism is about doing lots of things at once.
